score.explanation: Your Wi-Fi connection is performing well overall but may still experience occasional dropouts due to network congestion.
score.trend_summary: Since last scan: download improved, upload stayed the same, ping improved, networks decreased.

latest_report.diagnosis: Your Wi-Fi is subject to moderate congestion, primarily on the 5GHz band where several other signals are competing. This could contribute to the random dropouts experienced.

performance.interpretation: Current speeds meet your ISP plan effectively, but the slightly high number of competing networks may impact reliability.

problems: High network congestion, especially on the 5GHz band.
Suboptimal channel selection for 2.4GHz and 5GHz bands.
Wireless signal dropouts causing unreliable connection.
fixes: Change the 2.4GHz channel to 6, which is currently the least congested.
Set the 5GHz channel to either 149 or 157 to minimize overlap with competing networks.
Consider enabling Band Steering (if available) to optimize device connection to the best available band.
Reposition the router to a more central location in your home to improve signal distribution.
If dropouts persist, explore QoS settings to prioritize gaming traffic.
